Cooked sweetcorn is a type of food that can be obtained by cooking sweetcorn on a fire or cooking range, requiring level 28 Cooking and granting 104 experience when successful. Players may burn the sweetcorn while cooking one, resulting in burnt sweetcorn; the burn rate while cooking these will decrease as players reach higher Cooking levels. It will stop burning entirely at Cooking level 54 on both ranges and fires. When eaten it heals 1+10% of total hitpoints, rounded down.

Cooked sweetcorn may also be put in a bowl (giving a bowl of sweetcorn), and then mixed with a cooked tuna, with a knife in your inventory at level 67 Cooking, to make tuna and corn. This mixture heals 13 hitpoints when eaten, but may also may be added to a baked potato with butter at level 68 Cooking. This makes a tuna potato, which heals 22 hitpoints.
